3 Create an account

<p>thecrag is a global database of rock climbing areas and routes. <a href="/processmap/signup">Signup</a> to get more out of the database. It's FREE TO JOIN.</p>

<p>Once you have created an account you will be able to:</p>
<ul>
  <li><p>Log your ascents as a permanent record of your climbing history;</p></li>
  <li><p>Keep track of ascents your friends are doing;</p></li>
  <li><p>Get climb recommendations based on your climbing profile; and</p></li>
  <li><p>Update the database to make it more accurate for the climbing community.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>Start logging your ascents and the whole community benefits. Every ascent logged is a micro input into climb statistics, including popularity and route quality. Because ascents are logged against registered climbs, all these micro inputs combine to produce a robust community picture of climbing in an area.</p>

<p>thecrag is the orignal site for logging ascents, operating since 1999, and is the only site to be logging ascents against a comprehensive list of registered routes. The database has over 170,000 routes, and over 400,000 ascents logged. </p>

<p><a href="/processmap/signup">Join us</a> and help make it better for the whole climbing community.</p>


